All Classes

Class Summary 
Class Description
Board
Board This class deals with initializing and rendering all necessary game objects, using an integer array as input for reference.
Bonus
Bonus This class implements the bonus rewards for the game
Enemy
Enemy This class renders the enemies and contains all of the relevant variables and constructors including the distance between the enemies and the player
Exit
Exit This class implements the exit for the game
Game
Game This class deals with creating a new board and player, as well as various game states, running, starting, stopping, updating the game, checking if the game is over, collisions, checking if keys are pressed, and drawing various screens such as the starting menu or game over screen
ImageData
Image Data This class contains the integer representations of all of our sprites for the game, gets them and places them on the map, as well as dealing with the floor and direction.
Key
Key This class implements the key fragments for the game
Main
Main This class creates a new Game and a new Jframe.
Player
Player This class renders the player and contains all of the relevant variables and constructors
playerAnimation
playerAnimation This class deals with player animation
Punishment
Punishment This class implements the punishments for the game
Wall
Wall This class implements the walls for the game
